properties.abstract: Ready for playing with the views? The path from Bad Ragaz to Pardiel winds its way up through lovely forests. Whenever the trees allow for the view to open up, you can catch a glimpse of the Gonzen, Falknis and Regitzer Spitz mountains. After a rest, the descent on forest trails and paths beckons.
properties.description:
The present route is an original mountain bike route that starts in Bad Ragaz. On a small, averagely steep but well-driveable mountain road bikers will reach Pardiel. The ascent on almost car-free mountain roads is physically demanding. If you want to avoid this climb, you can take the Pizol-Pardiel cable car. On their way they can enjoy magnificent views of Seeztal, Rhine valley, Liechtenstein and Bndner Herrschaft.

Once you have made it to the top, several inns with panoramic terraces invite you to take a break. Several mountain inns are well on your disposal to serve delicious food and drinks so that you can regain energy and enjoy a wonderful view. A charging station for e-bikes is available at the Edelweiss panorama restaurant. Prodkopf is a viewpoint close by, which provides an especially marvellous panorama view. The fragments of the views spotted during the ascent now come together forming a picture. 

The descent on the short section to Muttberg is not difficult, but takes you over hill and dale and makes for good fun. The route continues via a forest path and goes back to the health resort Bad Ragaz. The alleviating thermal spa water of Tamina Therme is a source of relaxation after an eventful bike trip.
